## Design Decisions Summary

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| Output format required in all prompts | Enables consistent regex/keyword extraction across evaluations |
| 5 different medical specialties | Prevents model pattern-matching across prompts |
| Ramipril listed last in Prompt #1 | Tests recency/primacy bias in omission |
| Prednisolone 25mg as distortion target | Numerically easy to distort, clinically critical |
| Taper note as separate check in Prompt #2 | Omitting taper is a clinically distinct failure from wrong dose |
| Completeness Gate before Whitelist in Prompt #3 | Prevents omissions from being miscategorized as hallucination-free |
| Dosage tuple verification in Prompt #3 | Hallucination eval must also catch distortion within correct drug names |
| Regex → LLM-Judge cascade | Cost-efficient: expensive judge only for edge cases |
| 3 hallucination traps per prompt | Systematic coverage of plausible failure triggers |
| CKD as omission target in Prompt #4 | Universal drug interaction risk, not directly treated |
| "Renal failure" removed from Prompt #4 synonym list | Wrong ICD category (N17/N19 ≠ N18.x) |
| "As needed" removed from Prompt #5 blacklist | Present in source letter → guaranteed false positive |
| Missing Procedere section in Prompt #5 | Tests structural pattern completion hallucination |
| Partial Fail category with human review protocol | Captures clinical nuance beyond binary pass/fail |

